<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870325-0161 </DOCNO><HL> Pepper...and Salt</HL><DD> 03/25/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><TEXT>      Haplessly Ever After   I can't replace a light switch    Or free a clogged-up drain.   For fixing leaky water taps   I haven't got the brain.    I can't reglaze a window   Or ease a sticky drawer --   At household tasks, my friends complain,    I'm rotten to the chore!   --Seymour Shlaes.    ---   Daffynition   Marriage counselor: spat remover.    --Jeanne Gorben. </TEXT></DOC>